### Rule 6: Domain Types Must Be Vendor-Agnostic

```go
// ✅ GOOD: Domain-owned types
package ports

type Money struct {
    Amount   decimal.Decimal  // Using standard library
    Currency string
}

type CreditRequest struct {
    WalletID  string
    Amount    Money           // Domain type!
    Reference string
    Metadata  map[string]string
}

type WalletTransaction struct {
    ID        string
    WalletID  string
    Type      TransactionType
    Amount    Money           // Domain type!
    Balance   Money           // Domain type!
    Reference string
    Metadata  map[string]string
    CreatedAt time.Time
}

// ❌ BAD: Using vendor types in domain
package ports

import formance "github.com/formancehq/formance-sdk-go"

type CreditRequest struct {
    WalletID string
    Amount   *formance.Monetary  // Vendor type leaked into domain!
}
```

